      "content": "Separating the doses by 2 hours is a common strategy, but clarithromycin's interaction with simvastatin is so severe that timing alone rarely prevents dangerous toxicity. Given your current symptoms, you should prioritize your health and contact your doctor immediately to discuss switching your statin rather than risking a life-threatening reaction. There is no safe way to self-manage this interaction without professional guidance.",
